What you need to know:  Jepchirchir was a late inclusion in the women’s marathon team for the World Athletics Championships starting Friday in Eugene, Oregon, United StatesJepchichir said it was on Monday last week when she started having some discomfort with her hip that was swollen, forcing her to inform the team managementThe team now remains with defending champion Ruth Chepng’etich, Paris Marathon champion Judith Jeptum, and Angela Tanui, who finished fourth at this year's Tokyo Marathon on March 6